column1: Accept food from friends or family
Borrow money from friends and family
Buy foods that don't go bad quickly (e.g., pasta, beans, rice, canned foods)
Get food from a food pantry or soup kitchen
Sign up for or continue participation in a government program, such as SNAP, USDA’s monthly commodity supplemental food program
Sign up for or continue participation in a senior food program, such as senior food box program
Stretch the food that I have by eating less
